               <head>Judeo-Persian commentaries (fragments)</head>
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
                  <summary>Fragments of Judeo-Persian commentaries on verses from the Pentateuch and some
              other biblical books.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jpr">Hebrew, Persian</textLang>
                  <msItem class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
                     <locus from="1r" to="123v" />
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perushim</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he">פרושים</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Based on their content and linguistic and paleographic features, these
                  manuscripts are datable to the 11th-12th centuries, and not to the 16th century or
                  later as suggested by Margoliouth (information provided by Ofir Haim).</p>
                        <p>So far, it has not been possible to determine the identity of the authors of
                  these manuscripts and/or the place of their composition or copying. However, it is
                  quite possible to assume that the authors were Karaite since Hebrew Karaite terms
                  (e.g. רועי גלות, משכילים etc.) are attested in these texts. Another interesting
                  feature of these texts is their affinity to the commentaries of the Karaite Yefet
                  ben 'Eli. (Information provided by Ofir Haim).</p>
                     </note>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="1r" to="32v" />
                        <title>Commentary on Num. 8:12-12:16</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="33r" to="63r" />
                        <title>Commentary on Hosea 2</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>Ff. 62r-63r are written by a different hand; mostly vocalized.</p>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus n="64r" />
                        <title>Elegy</title>
                        <note>
                           <p />
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="64v" to="70r" />
                        <title>Introduction to the commentary on Proverbs</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>F. 64v: <quote xml:lang="he">בשם יי אתחיל לכתוב ספר
                  משלי</quote>.
                           </p>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="70v" to="71r" />
                        <title>Glossary of difficult words from the first weekly portion of Genesis</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>Judeo-Persian text vocalized.</p>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="72v" to="75r" />
                        <title>Sermon(?) on Is. 40:1</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>F. 72v: <quote xml:lang="he">בשם 'י פתרון נחמו ינחם יי בנחמת ציון וירושלם
                      עם צדיקים למפתירו</quote>.
                           </p>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="75v" to="80r" />
                        <title>Sermon(?) on the Ten Commandments</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>Judeo-Persian text vocalized.</p>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="80v" to="123v" />
                        <title>Sermon(?) on Is. 40:1</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>F. 80v: <quote xml:lang="he">תפסיר ואלה שמות</quote>.
                           </p>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
